{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882542743,"sessionID":"ses_28528b7ebffeFv9c7JJQBGBX9F","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad7cd53001FA1OHB2TZzuPu3","messageID":"msg_d7ad7bb9e001CzjauSJC0YFG3z","sessionID":"ses_28528b7ebffeFv9c7JJQBGBX9F","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_a50f5218ec9b4668b1a01d72","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/Makefile.design.md","content":"# Design: AR-033 — Makefile 构建目标体系\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation for the Makefile build target system in AgentCube. The Makefile provides a comprehensive set of targets for building, pushing, testing, and managing Docker container images across multiple components (Workload Manager, Router, Picod), with support for multi-architecture builds, Kind cluster integration, and image validation.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Structure\n\n```\nroot/\n├── Makefile                          # Main build system\n├── deployment/\n│   └── docker/\n│       ├── Dockerfile                # Workload Manager Dockerfile\n│       ├── Dockerfile.router         # Router Dockerfile\n│       ├── Dockerfile.picod          # Picod Dockerfile\n│       ├── test/\n│       │   ├── validate.sh           # Image validation script\n│       │   ├── build_test.sh         # Build verification tests\n│       │   └── runtime_test.sh       # Runtime verification tests\n│       └── validate.sh               # Main validation entry point\n└── bin/                              # Build artifacts\n```\n\n### Target Categories\n\nThe Makefile organizes targets into logical categories:\n\n1. **Build Targets** - `docker-build-*`\n2. **Push Targets** - `docker-push-*`\n3. **Kind Integration** - `kind-load-*`\n4. **Multi-architecture** - `docker-buildx-*`\n5. **Test & Validate** - `docker-test*`, `docker-validate*`\n6. **Cleanup** - `docker-clean`\n7. **Help** - `help`\n\n### Integration Points\n\n- **Docker** - Primary build and runtime engine\n- **Docker Buildx** - Multi-architecture builds\n- **Kind** - Local Kubernetes testing\n- **Git** - Version tagging and commit SHA injection\n- **Shell Scripts** - Test and validation automation\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Configuration Variables\n\n```makefile\n# Docker configuration\nDOCKER_REGISTRY ?= ghcr.io/volcano-sh\nDOCKER_TAG ?= latest\nVERSION ?= $(shell git describe --tags --always --dirty 2>/dev/null || echo \"dev\")\nCOMMIT_SHA ?= $(shell git rev-parse --short HEAD 2>/dev/null || echo \"unknown\")\n\n# Image names\nWORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/workloadmanager\nROUTER_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/router\nPICOD_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/picod\n```\n\n### Image Metadata\n\nEach Docker image receives the following metadata via build arguments:\n\n| Variable | Source | Description |\n|----------|--------|-------------|\n| `VERSION` | `git describe --tags --always --dirty` | Git-based version string |\n| `COMMIT_SHA` | `git rev-parse --short HEAD` | Short commit hash |\n| `DOCKER_TAG` | Environment or default `latest` | Image tag |\n| `DOCKER_REGISTRY` | Environment or default `ghcr.io/volcano-sh` | Container registry |\n\n### Target Dependency Graph\n\n```\ndocker-build-all\n├── docker-build-workloadmanager\n├── docker-build-router\n└── docker-build-picod\n\ndocker-push-all\n├── docker-push-workloadmanager\n├── docker-push-router\n└── docker-push-picod\n\nkind-load-all\n├── kind-load-workloadmanager\n├── kind-load-router\n└── kind-load-picod\n\ndocker-buildx-all\n├── docker-buildx-workloadmanager\n├── docker-buildx-router\n└── docker-buildx-picod\n\ndocker-validate\n├── docker-validate-workloadmanager\n├── docker-validate-router\n└── docker-validate-picod\n\ndocker-test\n├── docker-test-build\n└── docker-test-runtime\n\ndocker-clean (independent)\nhelp (independent)\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Build Target Contract\n\n**Pattern**: `docker-build-<component>`\n\n**Input Variables**:\n- `DOCKER_TAG` (optional, default: `latest`)\n- `VERSION` (auto-detected from git)\n- `COMMIT_SHA` (auto-detected from git)\n\n**Behavior**:\n1. Invoke `docker build` with component-specific Dockerfile\n2. Pass build arguments: `VERSION`, `COMMIT_SHA`\n3. Tag image with three tags: `DOCKER_TAG`, `COMMIT_SHA`, `VERSION`\n4. Output success message with image name\n\n**Example**:\n```bash\nmake docker-build-workloadmanager DOCKER_TAG=v1.0.0\n```\n\n### Push Target Contract\n\n**Pattern**: `docker-push-<component>`\n\n**Prerequisites**: \n- Docker authentication configured for `DOCKER_REGISTRY`\n- Image exists locally (run build target first)\n\n**Behavior**:\n1. Push all three tags to registry\n2. Output confirmation messages\n\n**Example**:\n```bash\nmake docker-push-all DOCKER_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/volcano-sh\n```\n\n### Kind Load Target Contract\n\n**Pattern**: `kind-load-<component>`\n\n**Prerequisites**:\n- Kind cluster running\n- Image exists locally\n\n**Behavior**:\n1. Load image into Kind cluster's containerd storage\n2. Enable pod scheduling with local image\n\n**Example**:\n```bash\nmake kind-load-all\n```\n\n### Multi-architecture Build Contract\n\n**Pattern**: `docker-buildx-<component>`\n\n**Prerequisites**:\n- Docker Buildx enabled\n- Builder instance configured for multi-arch\n- Registry authentication\n\n**Platforms**: `linux/amd64`, `linux/arm64`\n\n**Behavior**:\n1. Build multi-arch image using buildx\n2. Push directly to registry (no local load)\n3. Create manifest list with both architectures\n\n**Example**:\n```bash\nmake docker-buildx-router DOCKER_TAG=multi-arch-test\n```\n\n### Validate Target Contract\n\n**Pattern**: `docker-validate[-<component>]`\n\n**Prerequisites**:\n- Image exists locally\n\n**Behavior**:\n1. Invoke `deployment/docker/test/validate.sh` with image name\n2. Check image size, security configuration, labels\n3. Report validation results\n\n**Example**:\n```bash\nmake docker-validate\n```\n\n### Test Target Contract\n\n**Targets**: `docker-test-build`, `docker-test-runtime`, `docker-test`\n\n**Prerequisites**:\n- Docker daemon running\n- Build scripts executable\n\n**Behavior**:\n1. `docker-test-build`: Run build verification tests\n2. `docker-test-runtime`: Run runtime behavior tests\n3. Report pass/fail status\n\n**Example**:\n```bash\nmake docker-test\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Variable Fallback Chain\n\n```makefile\n# Git-based version detection with fallback\nVERSION ?= $(shell git describe --tags --always --dirty 2>/dev/null || echo \"dev\")\n\n# Commit SHA with fallback\nCOMMIT_SHA ?= $(shell git rev-parse --short HEAD 2>/dev/null || echo \"unknown\")\n```\n\n### Error Suppression Patterns\n\nFor cleanup operations, use `-` prefix to ignore failures:\n\n```makefile\ndocker-clean:\n\t-docker rmi $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) 2>/dev/null || true\n```\n\n### Validation Error Handling\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# deployment/docker/test/validate.sh\n\nset -e  # Exit on first error\n\nIMAGE=\"$1\"\n\nif [ -z \"$IMAGE\" ]; then\n    echo \"Error: Image name required\"\n    exit 1\nfi\n\n# Check image exists\nif ! docker image inspect \"$IMAGE\" > /dev/null 2>&1; then\n    echo \"Error: Image $IMAGE not found\"\n    exit 1\nfi\n\n# Size check (example: max 200MB)\nSIZE=$(docker image inspect \"$IMAGE\" --format='{{.Size}}')\nMAX_SIZE=$((200 * 1024 * 1024))\nif [ \"$SIZE\" -gt \"$MAX_SIZE\" ]; then\n    echo \"Error: Image size exceeds limit (${SIZE} > ${MAX_SIZE})\"\n    exit 1\nfi\n```\n\n### Docker Command Error Handling\n\nAll docker commands should handle failures gracefully:\n\n```makefile\ndocker-build-workloadmanager:\n\t@if ! docker build \\\n\t\t-f deployment/docker/Dockerfile \\\n\t\t--build-arg VERSION=$(VERSION) \\\n\t\t--build-arg COMMIT_SHA=$(COMMIT_SHA) \\\n\t\t-t $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) \\\n\t\t.; then \\\n\t\techo \"Error: Build failed\"; \\\n\t\texit 1; \\\n\tfi\n```\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests (Build Verification)\n\n**File**: `deployment/docker/test/build_test.sh`\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# Test 1: Verify Dockerfile syntax\ntest_dockerfile_syntax() {\n    local dockerfile=\"$1\"\n    if ! docker build --check -f \"$dockerfile\" . 2>/dev/null; then\n        echo \"FAIL: Dockerfile syntax error: $dockerfile\"\n        return 1\n    fi\n    echo \"PASS: Dockerfile syntax valid: $dockerfile\"\n}\n\n# Test 2: Verify build arguments\ntest_build_args() {\n    local image=$(docker build \\\n        -f deployment/docker/Dockerfile \\\n        --build-arg VERSION=test-version \\\n        --build-arg COMMIT_SHA=test-sha \\\n        -q .)\n    \n    # Verify labels\n    local version=$(docker inspect \"$image\" --format='{{index .Config.Labels \"version\"}}')\n    if [ \"$version\" != \"test-version\" ]; then\n        echo \"FAIL: Version label mismatch\"\n        return 1\n    fi\n    echo \"PASS: Build arguments applied correctly\"\n}\n\n# Run all tests\ntest_dockerfile_syntax \"deployment/docker/Dockerfile\"\ntest_dockerfile_syntax \"deployment/docker/Dockerfile.router\"\ntest_dockerfile_syntax \"deployment/docker/Dockerfile.picod\"\ntest_build_args\n```\n\n### Integration Tests (Runtime Verification)\n\n**File**: `deployment/docker/test/runtime_test.sh`\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# Test 1: Container startup\ntest_container_startup() {\n    local container_id=$(docker run -d \"$IMAGE\" sleep 30)\n    if [ -z \"$container_id\" ]; then\n        echo \"FAIL: Container failed to start\"\n        return 1\n    fi\n    \n    # Wait for health check\n    sleep 5\n    if ! docker exec \"$container_id\" pgrep -x \"workloadmanager\" > /dev/null; then\n        echo \"FAIL: Process not running\"\n        docker rm -f \"$container_id\"\n        return 1\n    fi\n    \n    docker rm -f \"$container_id\"\n    echo \"PASS: Container startup successful\"\n}\n\n# Test 2: Environment variable injection\ntest_env_vars() {\n    local container_id=$(docker run -d \\\n        -e REDIS_ADDR=\"redis:6379\" \\\n        -e REDIS_PASSWORD=\"test\" \\\n        \"$IMAGE\" sleep 30)\n    \n    local redis_addr=$(docker exec \"$container_id\" env | grep REDIS_ADDR)\n    if [ -z \"$redis_addr\" ]; then\n        echo \"FAIL: Environment variables not injected\"\n        docker rm -f \"$container_id\"\n        return 1\n    fi\n    \n    docker rm -f \"$container_id\"\n    echo \"PASS: Environment variables injected\"\n}\n```\n\n### Validation Tests\n\n**File**: `deployment/docker/test/validate.sh`\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\nIMAGE=\"$1\"\n\necho \"Validating $IMAGE...\"\n\n# Test 1: Image exists\necho -n \"Checking image exists... \"\nif docker image inspect \"$IMAGE\" > /dev/null 2>&1; then\n    echo \"PASS\"\nelse\n    echo \"FAIL\"\n    exit 1\nfi\n\n# Test 2: Size check\necho -n \"Checking image size... \"\nSIZE=$(docker image inspect \"$IMAGE\" --format='{{.Size}}')\nSIZE_MB=$((SIZE / 1024 / 1024))\nif [ \"$SIZE_MB\" -lt 200 ]; then\n    echo \"PASS (${SIZE_MB}MB)\"\nelse\n    echo \"FAIL (${SIZE_MB}MB exceeds 200MB limit)\"\n    exit 1\nfi\n\n# Test 3: Required labels\necho -n \"Checking labels... \"\nfor label in version commit-sha; do\n    if ! docker inspect \"$IMAGE\" --format=\"{{index .Config.Labels \\\"$label\\\"}}\" | grep -q .; then\n        echo \"FAIL (missing $label)\"\n        exit 1\n    fi\ndone\necho \"PASS\"\n\n# Test 4: Security scan (trivy example)\necho -n \"Running security scan... \"\nif command -v trivy > /dev/null; then\n    if trivy image --exit-code 1 \"$IMAGE\" > /dev/null 2>&1; then\n        echo \"PASS\"\n    else\n        echo \"FAIL (vulnerabilities found)\"\n        exit 1\n    fi\nelse\n    echo \"SKIP (trivy not installed)\"\nfi\n\necho \"\"\necho \"Validation passed!\"\n```\n\n### Kind Integration Tests\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# Test: Load image to Kind and verify pod scheduling\n\nCLUSTER_NAME=\"agentcube-test\"\n\n# Create Kind cluster\nkind create cluster --name \"$CLUSTER_NAME\"\n\n# Load image\nmake kind-load-workloadmanager\n\n# Deploy test pod\nkubectl apply -f - <<EOF\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Pod\nmetadata:\n  name: test-workloadmanager\nspec:\n  containers:\n  - name: workloadmanager\n    image: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager:latest\n  restartPolicy: Never\nEOF\n\n# Wait for pod to start\nkubectl wait --for=condition=Ready pod/test-workloadmanager --timeout=60s\n\nif [ $? -eq 0 ]; then\n    echo \"PASS: Image loaded and pod scheduled successfully\"\n    kind delete cluster --name \"$CLUSTER_NAME\"\n    exit 0\nelse\n    echo \"FAIL: Pod failed to schedule\"\n    kind delete cluster --name \"$CLUSTER_NAME\"\n    exit 1\nfi\n```\n\n### Test Matrix\n\n| Test Category | Coverage | Frequency |\n|---------------|----------|-----------|\n| Build verification | 100% of Dockerfiles | Every build |\n| Runtime behavior | Critical paths | CI/CD |\n| Validation | Size, labels, security | Pre-push |\n| Kind integration | Full deployment cycle | CI/CD |\n\n## Environment Configuration\n\n### Required Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `DOCKER_REGISTRY` | No | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh` | Container registry |\n| `DOCKER_TAG` | No | `latest` | Image tag |\n| `DOCKER_REGISTRY_USERNAME` | For push | - | Registry username |\n| `DOCKER_REGISTRY_PASSWORD` | For push | - | Registry password/token |\n\n### Optional Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|\n| `VERSION` | Override auto-detected version |\n| `COMMIT_SHA` | Override auto-detected commit SHA |\n| `DOCKER_BUILDKIT` | Enable BuildKit (recommended: `1`) |\n| `DOCKER_BUILD_CONTEXT` | Custom build context path |\n\n### Authentication Setup\n\n```bash\n# GitHub Container Registry\necho \"$GITHUB_TOKEN\" | docker login ghcr.io -u \"$GITHUB_USERNAME\" --password-stdin\n\n# Alternative: Use environment variables\nexport DOCKER_REGISTRY_USERNAME=\"your-username\"\nexport DOCKER_REGISTRY_PASSWORD=\"your-token\"\n```\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\nroot/\n├── Makefile                          # Main build system (237 lines)\n├── deployment/\n│   └── docker/\n│       ├── Dockerfile                # Workload Manager base image\n│       ├── Dockerfile.router         # Router image\n│       ├── Dockerfile.picod          # Picod image\n│       └── test/\n│           ├── validate.sh           # Image validation (size, security, labels)\n│           ├── build_test.sh         # Build verification tests\n│           ├── runtime_test.sh       # Runtime behavior tests\n│           └── kind_test.sh          # Kind cluster integration tests\n└── bin/                              # Build output directory\n```\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n### Version Detection\n\nThe Makefile uses git to automatically detect version information:\n\n```makefile\nVERSION ?= $(shell git describe --tags --always --dirty 2>/dev/null || echo \"dev\")\nCOMMIT_SHA ?= $(shell git rev-parse --short HEAD 2>/dev/null || echo \"unknown\")\n```\n\n**Fallback behavior**:\n- If git is not available: `VERSION=dev`, `COMMIT_SHA=unknown`\n- If in dirty working tree: `VERSION=<tag>-<commits>-g<sha>-dirty`\n- If no tags exist: `VERSION=<sha>`\n\n### Image Tagging Strategy\n\nEach build produces three tags for flexibility:\n\n1. **`DOCKER_TAG`** - Configurable tag (default: `latest`)\n2. **`COMMIT_SHA`** - Immutable commit-based tag\n3. **`VERSION`** - Git describe-based version tag\n\nThis enables:\n- Development: Use `latest` tag\n- CI/CD: Use `COMMIT_SHA` for traceability\n- Releases: Use `VERSION` for semantic versioning\n\n### Multi-architecture Support\n\nBuildx targets use the following configuration:\n\n```makefile\ndocker buildx build \\\n    --platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 \\\n    --push \\\n    -t $(IMAGE):$(TAG) \\\n    .\n```\n\n**Notes**:\n- `--push` required (multi-arch images cannot be loaded locally)\n- Requires buildx builder with multi-arch support\n- Creates manifest list automatically\n\n### Kind Integration\n\nKind load targets use:\n\n```bash\nkind load docker-image $(IMAGE):$(TAG)\n```\n\n**Limitations**:\n- Only loads single architecture (matches Kind node architecture)\n- Does not load multi-arch manifest lists\n- Image must exist in local Docker daemon first\n\n### Cleanup Strategy\n\nThe `docker-clean` target uses defensive deletion:\n\n```makefile\n-docker rmi $(IMAGE):$(TAG) 2>/dev/null || true\n```\n\n**Rationale**:\n- `-` prefix: Ignore command failure\n- `2>/dev/null`: Suppress error messages\n- `|| true`: Ensure Makefile continues even if image doesn't exist\n\nThis makes cleanup idempotent and safe to run multiple times.\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n1. **Registry Authentication** - Use tokens, not passwords; store in CI/CD secrets\n2. **Image Signing** - Consider implementing cosign or Docker Content Trust\n3. **Vulnerability Scanning** - Integrate trivy or similar in CI/CD\n4. **Build Isolation** - Use BuildKit for reproducible builds\n5. **Secret Management** - Never hardcode secrets in Dockerfiles; use build secrets or multi-stage builds\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| Docker | ≥20.10 | Container build and runtime |\n| Docker Buildx | ≥0.6 | Multi-architecture builds |\n| Kind | ≥0.17 | Local Kubernetes testing |\n| Git | ≥2.0 | Version detection |\n| Bash | ≥4.0 | Test scripts |\n| trivy | Optional | Security scanning |\n\n## Migration Notes\n\n### From Manual Docker Commands\n\n**Before**:\n```bash\ndocker build -f deployment/docker/Dockerfile -t ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager:latest .\ndocker push ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager:latest\n```\n\n**After**:\n```bash\nmake docker-build-workloadmanager\nmake docker-push-workloadmanager\n```\n\n**Benefits**:\n- Automatic version tagging\n- Consistent build arguments\n- Integrated validation and testing\n\n### Breaking Changes\n\nNone - this is a new implementation.\n\n## Examples\n\n### Development Workflow\n\n```bash\n# Build all images\nmake docker-build-all\n\n# Load to Kind for testing\nmake kind-load-all\n\n# Run tests\nmake docker-test\n\n# Deploy to Kind\nkubectl apply -k manifests/\n```\n\n### CI/CD Pipeline\n\n```bash\n# Build and validate\nmake docker-build-all\nmake docker-validate\n\n# Push to registry\necho \"$GITHUB_TOKEN\" | docker login ghcr.io -u \"$GITHUB_USERNAME\" --password-stdin\nmake docker-push-all\n\n# Load to test cluster\nkind create cluster --name test\nmake kind-load-all\n\n# Run integration tests\n./testing/integration/run_tests.sh\n```\n\n### Multi-architecture Release\n\n```bash\n# Build and push multi-arch images\nmake docker-buildx-all DOCKER_TAG=v1.0.0\n\n# Verify manifest\ndocker manifest inspect ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager:v1.0.0\n```\n\n### Clean Build\n\n```bash\n# Clean local images\nmake docker-clean\n\n# Rebuild from scratch\nmake docker-build-all DOCKER_TAG=dev\n```\n\n## References\n\n- `Makefile` - Current implementation (237 lines)\n- `deployment/docker/Dockerfile` - Workload Manager Dockerfile\n- `deployment/docker/Dockerfile.router` - Router Dockerfile\n- `deployment/docker/Dockerfile.picod` - Picod Dockerfile\n- AR-030 - Helm Chart deployment (uses images built by this Makefile)\n- AR-031 - RBAC configuration (independent of build system)\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/Makefile.design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/Makefile.design.md","time":{"start":1775882542729,"end":1775882542739}}}}
